  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study compares several different antiretroviral adherence measures, including digital&#xD;
      pills, in HIV+ individuals who are maintained on opioid analgesics.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study compares digital pills, electronic pill bottles, self-report, and dried blood&#xD;
      spots, in measuring adherence to antiretroviral medications containing emtricitabine and&#xD;
      tenofovir. The study sites are Jackson Memorial Hospital and Fenway Community Health.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
